learning_outcomes.en:
Upon completion of this course, students:
1)	are capable of planning, carrying out, documenting and presenting, either in academic writing or by means of alternative expressive means, the results of a research, development or creative project in their chosen field of specialization either individually or members of a team;
2)	know how to critically use research literature and other secondary sources in their chosen field of specialization;
3)	are capable of demonstrating comprehensive knowledge of and to discuss complex problems in their chosen field of specialization.
